postcontent:
Up for Auction is an amazing 13mm GYRO JET Mark 1 Model B Rocket Pistol. Pistol was made in 1966 by MBA in San Ramon, California. To give you an idea of who made it: Robert Maitland was a Nuclear Physicist at Lawrence Livermore Laboratory. Just South of San Ramon, California. This was made before we went to the moon and he developed this to be use in the confines of outer space. But not just outer space and on the ground but underwater too. This was truly remarkable piece of equipment. Plus it was the launching platform for the included three (3) solid fuel rockets. 

Besides that if you really want to look it up go to the History Channel on you tube and type in Gyro Jet you will see one being fired. 

Back to this interesting rocket pistol. 

The 13mm Gyro Jet pistol here is #169 of 1000 and is one of 12 in bright nickle. It was made in early 1966 and is nearly perfect although it is missing one scale (grip panel). It makes me laugh because it has an On/Off Switch instead of a Fire/Safe Selector like the later 12mm Gyro Jet Rocket Pistols

title: Want To Buy:  WTB: hexie Mosin, M91, 91/30
location: almost anywhere in Jackson/Josephine county, Medford, Oregon
postcontent:
I'm looking for a specific type of Mosin. Not rare, just slightly less common. What I'm looking for is an M91, Dragoon/"ex-Dragoon" or possibly early (30-36) 91/30. Just in case you didn't know, the 4 digit number stamp is not coincidental, it is indeed the year your rifle was produced, so please check it. It will have a hex/octagon shaped receiver, blade type front sight and curved rear sight that measures in Arshins (an Arshin is 28 inches), not meters. Please see the pictures to see if you have what I'm looking for. I don't mind if the wood is all dinged up. I'd like it if there weren't massive chunks of it gone though. A bayonet and sling would be nice, but are not mandatory. I will want to chamber and eject one round, just to be sure. And yes, I'll show you my ODL if you like. Local buyer seeks local seller only please. No road trips for me. Plus cash for you if it's got a bent bolt. Please do send me pictures. I might buy 7.62x54 ammo depending on the price/condition.

I get people trying to sell me things other than what I am buying all the time. Please only reply if your rifle meets all the criteria I have mentioned. Someone else will buy your 1942/round receiver, trust me.

Please no:
round receivers
rifles made after 1936
M44s
91/59s
Type 53s
cut down barrels
parts guns or guns in parts
panic priced guns
guns that don't work
